00:19:50,223 --> 00:19:52,224
So that's why we're awarding because we've won a year.

201
00:19:54,865 --> 00:19:56,046
It's short.

202
00:19:56,386 --> 00:19:56,666
It's short.

203
00:19:56,686 --> 00:19:56,766
Yeah.

204
00:19:56,786 --> 00:19:56,946
Great.

205
00:19:56,966 --> 00:19:57,327
Thank you.

206
00:19:57,347 --> 00:19:58,667
I'm going to go to councilor Carviello.

207
00:20:04,646 --> 00:20:05,688
So you talked about the condos.

208
00:20:05,768 --> 00:20:09,154
Are we no longer going to be doing the condos?

209
00:20:13,262 --> 00:20:16,503
because I know we're gonna be getting the calls saying I pay the same tax as everybody else.

210
00:20:17,183 --> 00:20:35,248
Sure, so the preferred hauling system is a solution to that, to try to get lower rates, treat condominium buildings, kind of like they're not at a best practice, how they should be treated, but we understand that there's a certain service that they get now, but not all condominiums buildings in the city get that services.

211
00:20:36,088 --> 00:20:36,988
I know a lot of them.

212
00:20:37,008 --> 00:20:38,709
So we're trying to level the playing field,

213
00:20:39,129 --> 00:20:52,254
We understand that there may be some hits and some issues, but that's why we're trying to... Would there be negotiation with the condos to maybe go with the preferred hauler to take their waste also?

214
00:20:52,674 --> 00:20:52,874
Yes.

215
00:20:53,334 --> 00:20:53,574
Right.

216
00:20:53,654 --> 00:20:56,535
So the idea is that the preferred hauler will give us a price list.

217
00:20:56,635 --> 00:21:00,897
Right now, if you are an entity in Medford and you need waste service,

218
00:21:01,500 --> 00:21:06,842
You call up the different vendors, you have to figure out who the haulers are, and they give you different pricing.

219
00:21:07,282 --> 00:21:13,064
And sometimes they give you different pricing based on what you need, but sometimes they give you different pricing based on the day of the week.

220
00:21:14,465 --> 00:21:25,929
And so the idea would be that there would be a price list and they would know, and that everybody who wants a 12 yard dumpster would get charged in Medford the same rate for the 12 yard dumpster.

221
00:21:26,369 --> 00:21:28,490
And in theory, that's gonna be a lower rate

222
00:21:29,547 --> 00:21:36,971
under this contract than it would be today, because we would be recommending them as the Medford hauler.

223
00:21:37,372 --> 00:21:44,376
So they will give us lower rates for our resident, our community, because we're recommending them as the preferred hauler.

224
00:21:44,756 --> 00:21:46,337
So it'll be easy for these condos.

225
00:21:46,658 --> 00:21:48,199
There will be a list, a price list.

226
00:21:48,319 --> 00:21:49,800
They'll see what the price list is.

227
00:21:50,140 --> 00:21:53,642
They'll have somebody from waste management come out and say, how much waste are you generating?

228
00:21:53,703 --> 00:21:55,164
How many units in your building?

229
00:21:55,624 --> 00:21:57,005
Here's the size that you need.

230
00:21:57,465 --> 00:21:59,347
This is what you should have.

231
00:21:59,747 --> 00:22:00,607
And here's the price.

232
00:22:01,428 --> 00:22:03,650
So in theory, this is going to lower the rates.

233
00:22:03,710 --> 00:22:07,292
I mean, I can't promise any rates until we get our proposals.

234
00:22:07,833 --> 00:22:12,536
So the condo will have the opportunity to get the city negotiated price?

235
00:22:12,836 --> 00:22:13,797
Yes, absolutely.

236
00:22:14,553 --> 00:22:18,977
I am in favor of the extra yard waste because I know myself.

237
00:22:20,358 --> 00:22:22,960
Everybody's doing their own yard work.

238
00:22:23,621 --> 00:22:25,102
I am in favor of that.

239
00:22:26,283 --> 00:22:29,545
What is the feeling on the bulk items if people would have to pay for them?

240
00:22:30,646 --> 00:22:36,031
So the best practice for MassDEP is that you charge at least $5 an item.

241
00:22:36,471 --> 00:22:37,512
Right now we're paying $25 an item.

242
00:22:40,070 --> 00:22:43,855
We want to see what sort of proposal they're giving the different vendors are giving us.

243
00:22:44,696 --> 00:22:47,880
We do want to charge back to residents, at least the $5 an item.

244
00:22:50,323 --> 00:22:59,625
Part of the best practice system for the state is the more boxes you can check on their best practice list, the larger an annual grant that they will give you automatically.

245
00:23:00,545 --> 00:23:01,845
So it'll get us more points.

246
00:23:02,145 --> 00:23:03,465
So a larger grant for the city.

247
00:23:03,865 --> 00:23:11,587
We also hope that if people are charged some nominal amount, five or $10, they will put the item out.

248
00:23:11,847 --> 00:23:16,407
They won't forget to put it out because they actually paid for this service.

249
00:23:16,547 --> 00:23:18,668
It'll also help offset the cost to the city.

250
00:23:19,886 --> 00:23:28,512
Did the survey reflect people paying some type of nominal fee for the bulk items?

251
00:23:29,532 --> 00:23:30,953
Was that asked in the survey?

252
00:23:31,914 --> 00:23:33,395
So we did ask about that.

253
00:23:34,556 --> 00:23:37,498
So Madeline is here as a graduate student who worked with us on it.

254
00:23:37,518 --> 00:23:38,739
I actually wanted to acknowledge her.

255
00:23:38,799 --> 00:23:41,500
She had class, so had to come over late.

256
00:23:41,861 --> 00:23:44,662
And she really dug deep into the results of the survey.

257
00:23:45,003 --> 00:23:46,504
And we asked about that in the survey.

258
00:23:47,233 --> 00:23:49,994
Yeah, I think, to be honest, if people would be willing to pay more.

259
00:23:50,014 --> 00:23:52,095
Can you just, then they can hear you on the Zoom.

260
00:23:53,116 --> 00:23:54,836
You don't have to bend over.

261
00:23:56,017 --> 00:23:56,317
Yeah.

