We asked people if they would be willing to pay more for their trash collection services, and people mostly said they would need to have more information about that.

263
00:24:04,741 --> 00:24:07,722
They didn't say no, but they said maybe.

264
00:24:07,742 --> 00:24:09,803
I mean, if they pay maybe 50% or something.

265
00:24:10,123 --> 00:24:12,144
Or maybe we, what do we get?

266
00:24:13,645 --> 00:24:16,586
Two a year or four a year for the bulk items?

267
00:24:18,385 --> 00:24:19,886
bulk items?

268
00:24:19,906 --> 00:24:21,206
The ones that we pay for.

269
00:24:21,286 --> 00:24:22,207
Three every two weeks, I think.

270
00:24:22,407 --> 00:24:24,468
Three every two weeks.

271
00:24:24,548 --> 00:24:26,509
Yeah, so maybe if we cut that down also.

272
00:24:28,089 --> 00:24:30,851
I mean, how many bulk items do they get a week?

273
00:24:30,931 --> 00:24:36,473
Oh, I think we're up to like 17,000 or something for the year, but I don't know.

274
00:24:36,513 --> 00:24:39,314
It's a massive number, $400,000 worth, $25 per item.

275
00:24:39,735 --> 00:24:45,137
And also, we did talk about this at the workshop with the public as well, and I do recall feedback being

276
00:24:45,785 --> 00:24:51,648
uh, that five to $10 range is small enough to a lot of people that have a little bit of skin in the game.

277
00:24:51,768 --> 00:24:57,412
So they're going to be held responsible, you know, um, because we get about 10 to 15% of no-shows like Alicia was saying.

