00:27:20,695 --> 00:27:24,056
1,200 households are currently in Medford paying for this service.

312
00:27:24,596 --> 00:27:27,077
And so we do believe there is significantly more demand

313
00:27:27,557 --> 00:27:31,560
from people who either don't know it's an option or aren't willing to just pay.

314
00:27:31,580 --> 00:27:33,521
Will they continue to pay or will the city pay?

315
00:27:34,021 --> 00:27:37,283
The idea would be that we would pay and they would not have to pay any more.

316
00:27:37,323 --> 00:27:39,805
What do you think would the estimated cost of that be?

317
00:27:41,893 --> 00:27:44,774
We actually don't know what a citywide compost pick up.

