00:32:23,361 --> 00:32:30,744
We tried to work with the Chamber to find somewhere to put a dumpster where people can – where the businesses can do it.

377
00:32:30,824 --> 00:32:34,005
I mean, there's not many places in the squares.

378
00:32:34,025 --> 00:32:37,606
We're trying to keep all options at the table.

379
00:32:38,488 --> 00:32:43,670
Almost like we're trying to set up a framework so we can work with the hauler to really focus in on some of those solutions.

380
00:32:44,210 --> 00:32:47,431
Because right now, I think you're highlighting it.

381
00:32:47,872 --> 00:32:48,692
It's very challenging.

382
00:32:48,752 --> 00:32:48,992
Yeah.

383
00:32:49,372 --> 00:32:51,973
So yeah, like I said, that's always been a peep of mine living on.

384
00:32:52,353 --> 00:32:56,175
Yeah, that'd be something I'd like to see if they can get it at Nike.

385
00:32:58,036 --> 00:33:08,400
We keep that on the table, and I think that there's more to do there is really taking a close look at how we do the areas of limited space, commercial entities that want service.

386
00:33:08,740 --> 00:33:20,165
I think we're stepping in the right direction, having a preferred hauler, having it set up so we can assist with trying to figure out the best way to haul stuff out of our squares.

